Pfiesteria, humans: RFI(more questions than answers)
***************************************************
A ProMED mail posting
[See Pfiesteria pathogenesis 970904114125
Pfiesteria piscicida: a synopsis 970903121217
Pfiesteria toxin characterized 970827093903]
[1]
Date: Thu, 4 Sep 1997 19:46:39 +1000
From: browndav@ozemail.com.au (David Brown)

As you might imagine I have several patients that suffer the symptoms of
Pfiesteria poisoning. I wonder if it is possible to answer these questions:-
Have all the known cases been exposed to the live organism or have some
been at some distance from the presumed source of infection?
One of the articles mentions a typical pattern on an 'advanced brain scan',
what was this scan and what is the pattern?
Is there any diagnostic method available?
Has there been any advance on the mechanism of toxicity?
Are there any naturally occuring proteins with sequence homology?
I would appreciate any light you could shed on these questions.
[Although, research in humans has yielded definitive results yet, you be
able to piece together some clues to question by looking at the following
website, which was referenced in an earlier posting. If anyone has answers,
please let me know. - Mod pc.
<http://www2.ncsu.edu/unity/lockers/project/aquatic_botany/pfiest.html#Toxic
> ]
